# Cursor MCP Configuration
# This project includes an MCP server for JavaScript package management

## MCP Server Configuration
The JavaScript Package Manager MCP server provides tools for:
- Package search and installation
- Security vulnerability scanning  
- Bundle size analysis
- Dependency management across npm/yarn/pnpm

To use this MCP server in Cursor:
1. Build the project: `npm run build`
2. Configure in Cursor settings with:
   - Command: `node`
   - Args: `["./dist/index.js"]`
   - Working directory: This project root

## Available MCP Tools
- search_packages: Search npm registry
- install_packages/update_packages/remove_packages: Package management
- audit_dependencies: Security scanning
- check_bundle_size: Performance analysis
- dependency_tree: Visualize dependencies